---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Long-term Care | Medical Care and Rehabilitation"
  description="Information on long-term care options available to UK veterans through the Armed Forces Compensation Scheme. Learn about care facilities, home care services, and support for carers.">
  <div class="container my-5">
    <h1 class="display-4 mb-4">Long-term Care for Veterans</h1>
    <div class="row g-4">
      <div class="col-lg-8">
        <p class="lead">The Armed Forces Compensation Scheme (AFCS) is committed to providing comprehensive long-term care support for veterans with ongoing medical needs. This page outlines the various long-term care options and services available.</p>
        
        <h2 class="h3 mt-4">Specialised Care Facilities</h2>
        <p>For veterans requiring round-the-clock care, we offer access to specialised facilities:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Veterans' care homes with trained staff familiar with military-related conditions</li>
          <li>Rehabilitation centres for those recovering from severe injuries</li>
          <li>Specialist units for conditions like dementia or neurological disorders</li>
          <li>Respite care facilities for short-term stays</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2 class="h3 mt-4">Home Care Services</h2>
        <p>For those who prefer to receive care at home, we provide:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Personal care assistance for daily activities</li>
          <li>Nursing care for complex medical needs</li>
          <li>Occupational therapy to adapt homes for accessibility</li>
          <li>Meal preparation and nutrition support</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2 class="h3 mt-4">Support for Carers</h2>
        <p>We recognise the vital role of family carers and offer support including:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Respite care to give carers a break</li>
          <li>Training and education on caregiving skills</li>
          <li>Emotional support and counselling</li>
          <li>Financial advice and potential allowances for carers</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2 class="h3 mt-4">Regular Health Assessments</h2>
        <p>To ensure care remains appropriate, we provide:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Regular health and needs assessments</li>
          <li>Reviews of care plans and adjustments as needed</li>
          <li>Access to specialist consultations</li>
          <li>Coordination with other healthcare providers</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2 class="h3 mt-4">End-of-Life Care</h2>
        <p>For veterans nearing the end of life, we offer compassionate care including:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Palliative care services</li>
          <li>Support for advance care planning</li>
          <li>Emotional and spiritual support for veterans and their families</li>
          <li>Bereavement counselling for family members</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="col-lg-4">
        <div class="card bg-light mb-4">
          <div class="card-body">
            <h3 class="h5">Related Services</h3>
            <ul class="list-unstyled">
              <li><a href="/medical/rehabilitation" class="text-decoration-none">Rehabilitation Services</a></li>
              <li><a href="/support/mental-health" class="text-decoration-none">Mental Health Support</a></li>
              <li><a href="/financial/care-funding" class="text-decoration-none">Care Funding Advice</a></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card mb-4">
          <div class="card-body">
            <h3 class="h5">Care Assessment</h3>
            <p>Request a care needs assessment to determine the best long-term care options for you or your loved one.</p>
            <a href="/care-assessment" class="btn btn-primary">Request Assessment</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
